com.github.i49.hibiscus.schema

Interface ObjectType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CompositeType, JsonType

    public interface ObjectType
extends CompositeType
    One of built-in types representing JSON object which has TypeId.OBJECT as a type identifier.

    An instance of this type can be created through SchemaComponents.object(). The method receives instances of Property allowed to appear in the containing object.

    
 import static com.github.i49.hibiscus.schema.SchemaComponents.*;
 ObjectType t = object(property1, property2, ...);

    Restrictions on this type

    This type allows you to impose following restrictions on the value space.

    1. assertion

    1. assertion

    assertion allows you to make a arbitrary assertion on the values of this type.

    See Also:
    SchemaComponents

      • properties

        ObjectType properties(Property... properties)
        Declares all instances of Property which this object type may contain.

        If this method is called multiple times on the same instance, all previously declared properties are not preserved and removed from this type.

        Parameters:
        properties - the properties which object may contain. Each property cannot be null.
        Returns:
        this type.
        Throws:
        SchemaException - if one of properties specified is null.

      • moreProperties

        ObjectType moreProperties()
        Makes this object type accept properties not declared explicitly for this type. Invoking this method once relaxes the validation not to report problems even when objects of this type in JSON document have properties not declared. By default the validation reports problems when it found unknown properties of objects in JSON document.
        Returns:
        this type.
